  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the design and implementation of real-time systems involves rigorous scheduling algorithms and resource management techniques to ensure that timing constraints are consistently met.",
    "These systems must prioritize tasks based on their criticality, dynamically manage computational resources, and preempt lower-priority tasks when necessary to meet the deadlines of higher-priority ones.",
    "This intricate balancing act between resource allocation and task prioritization is fundamental to the operation of real-time systems.",
    "This necessity for precise timing introduces the concept of WCET analysis.",
    "WCET represents the maximum time required for a task to complete under any given set of conditions, serving as a critical metric for the design and validation of real-time systems."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}